---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = "April 2026";
---

<Layout
	title="Terms of Use — Metronome News"
	description="Terms of use for Metronome News. Content disclaimer, acceptable use, no warranty."
>
	<main class="static-page container">
		<header class="page-header">
			<div class="page-badge">Terms</div>
			<h1>Terms of Use</h1>
			<p class="page-tagline">The legal stuff. Short and readable.</p>
			<p class="last-updated">Last updated: <time>{lastUpdated}</time></p>
		</header>

		<div class="prose">
			<p class="lead">
				By using Metronome News, you agree to these terms. They exist to make expectations
				clear on both sides — what you can expect from us, and what we expect from visitors.
			</p>

			<h2>Content disclaimer</h2>
			<p>
				Articles on Metronome News are editorial content, not financial, legal, or investment
				advice. Cryptocurrency is risky. Do your own research. Consider consulting
				a licensed financial advisor before making decisions based on anything you read here
				or anywhere else on the internet.
			</p>
			<p>
				We work to be accurate but don't guarantee that any specific article is current,
				correct, or complete. If you find an error, please
				<a href="/contact">let us know</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>Intellectual property</h2>
			<p>
				All original articles, design, and code on Metronome News are copyrighted to
				the operator (raptor) unless stated otherwise. You may:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Read, share, and quote short excerpts for commentary or review.</li>
				<li>Link to articles freely.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>You may not:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Republish full articles without written permission.</li>
				<li>Use articles to train AI models without written permission.</li>
				<li>Pass off our content as your own.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Third-party content</h2>
			<p>
				Articles may quote, cite, or embed content from other sources (tweets, images,
				videos, quoted text). Such content remains the property of its original
				creators. If you believe content on Metronome News infringes your rights, please
				contact us — we respond to legitimate takedown requests promptly.
			</p>

			<h2>No warranty</h2>
			<p>
				Metronome News is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We don't guarantee:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>The accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of any article.</li>
				<li>Uptime or continuous availability.</li>
				<li>That the site is free from bugs, errors, or security issues.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				News content reflects the views of its author, not necessarily any advertisers,
				partners, or affiliates (currently we have none).
			</p>

			<h2>Acceptable use</h2>
			<p>Please don't:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Scrape the site in ways that overload our servers.</li>
				<li>Attempt to hack, disrupt, or abuse the service.</li>
				<li>Use the site to commit fraud or illegal activity.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
			<p>
				We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the site after changes
				constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. The "Last updated" date at the top
				of this page reflects the most recent revision.
			</p>

			<h2>Jurisdiction</h2>
			<p>
				These terms don't specify a jurisdiction — Metronome News is a one-person publication
				and any disputes are handled informally by email. If that's unacceptable for you,
				we apologize in advance, and suggest not using the site.
			</p>

			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about these terms? <a href="mailto:contact@metronome.news">contact@metronome.news</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.static-page {
		max-width: 780px;
		padding-block: 2.5rem 5rem;
	}

	.page-header {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}
	.page-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--color-accent);
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}
	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-weight: 800;
	}
	.page-tagline {
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	.last-updated {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--color-text-subtle);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.prose {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}
	.prose .lead {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--color-text);
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-size: 1.55rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}
	.prose p {
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}
	.prose ul {
		margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
	}
	.prose li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	.prose a {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 3px;
	}
	.prose a:hover {
		color: var(--color-accent-warm);
	}
	.prose strong {
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}
</style>